      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ESCOBAR NZ (10) has changed yards since he last raced for four-and-a-half months and looks forward enough for the return after a minor placing in a recent trial. Draws out a little on the second line so may need luck at some point but will have admirers. WICHITA KANSAS (2) did a good job to at his most recent outing when he drew on the back row and covered ground but stuck on to be beaten 5 metres into third at Stawell. This is stronger but he should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. THE MOUNTAIN (5) has to come into calculations having produced some decent efforts since coming from a similar barrier to this to win at Geelong last month. JUSTLIKEDAVE (9) may need some luck from this barrier but should find this easier than the latest attempt.",
